'He's got it with him now.'\par
'He never moves without it.'\par
'You'd think he'd have the sense to adopt some rude disguise.'\par
'You would indeed, sir, but the mental processes of a man like that are hard to follow.'\par
'Then there's no need for me to phone the local police?'\par
'None, sir. I will take him into custody.'\par
'You wouldn't like me to hit him over the head first with a Zulu knobkerrie?'\par
'Unnecessary, sir.'\par
'It might be safer.'\par
'No, sir, I am sure he will come quietly.'\par
'Well, have it your own way. But don't let him give you the slip.'\par
'I will be very careful, sir.'\par
'And shove him into a dungeon with dripping walls and see to it that he is well gnawed by rats.'\par
'Very good, sir.'\par
