'You've hit it, Jeeves. It's just what Pop Bassett would do. Nothing would please him better than to spoil Uncle Tom's day. What a man, Jeeves!'\par
'Yes, sir.'\par
'Would you like to have a mind like his?'\par
'No, sir.'\par
'Nor me. It just shows how being a magistrate saps the moral fibre. I remember thinking as I stood before him in the dock that he had a\par
